  "text": "In the antiretroviral-treated patients, the singlecopy assay determined that 77% of samples had viraemia detectable at >1 HIV-1 RNA copy/ml [CITATION_1] . By comparison, approximately 75% of elite controllers had measurable low-level viraemia. In a crosssectional analysis, mean viraemia values did not differ significantly between patients on suppressive therapy (0.50 log 10 copies/ml, or 3 copies/ml) and all elite controllers (0.49 log 10 copies/ml; P=0.95). However, between-patient variability was much greater among elite controllers than among those controlling HIV-1 with antiretrovirals (P<0.0001).",
